summary: Mcu idea: Avengers teaching other Avengers hero stuff
body:
Mcu idea: Avengers teaching other Avengers hero stuff

Natasha training Parker in more advanced combat. Him asking ‘is this gonna kill the guy? Cause I don’t want that.’ Natasha replies, ‘Okay, we’ll skip that move then.’

Dr Strange introducing Rhodes to meditation and other magic stuff. A year later he doesn’t need Tony’s exoskeleton to walk.

Sam and Thor sky racing to see how to improve one another’s flying.

T’Challa & Shuri on the Sheild hellicarrier for 12 minuets and giving Nick a list of problems/improvements before talking about movies.

Scott & Clint just…hanging out being dads as their kids play.

The Guardians taking Steve, Tony, Parker & Shuri to other planets. Captain & Ironman are being professional while the teens are just

blog.name: oxymitch
blog.title: Whatever Mitch
blog.description:
I am Mitch of Singapore, also an Ace. I enjoy reading superhero comics (especially Marvel); comic books aren't just for boys, girls read it too. However, I have no interest in any Marvel movie due to my jaded attitude, so I prefer Marvel cartoons like 90s X-Men TAS and Avengers EMH. 
Those Marvel comics I love reading are New Warriors, X-Men, Young Avengers, X-Factor, Avengers (not that Bendis era), Generation X, Avengers Academy and X-Force. 
Big fan of New Warriors and X-Men. 
My Favourite Marvel characters are...GAMBIT (Remy LeBeau), JUBILEE (Jubilation Lee), SPEEDBALL (Robbie Baldwin), WICCAN (Billy Kaplan), JUSTICE (Vance Astrovik), ROGUE (Anna Marie), SPEED (Tommy Shepherd), NIGHTCRAWLER (Kurt Wagner), FIRESTAR (Angelica Jones), QUICKSILVER (Pietro Maximoff), SHE-HULK (Jennifer Walters), QUASAR (Wendell Vaughn) and COSMO the space dog.

summary: JMS (J. Michael Straczynski) did a tribute issue for 9/11 incident in a Spider-Man comic. Given that New York is a home to many...
caption:
JMS (J. Michael Straczynski) did a tribute issue for 9/11 incident in a Spider-Man comic. Given that New York is a home to many superheroes in Marvel Universe, I can see those writers/artists try to make a tribute for the tragedy. 

However, there were some problems in the comic; the superheroes have been used to the everyday destruction which are caused by fights with supervillains, monsters, the unpredictable raging Hulk or alien invaders. Firstly, the Avengers did fail to save a town in Washington DC from Kang’s attack in Kang Dynasty storyline so it should be nothing new about the superheroes moping about their failures. Secondly, why would Magneto the well-known Mutant supremacist or Doctor Doom the dictator of Latveria and archnemesis of Fantastic Four be present at the Ground Zero feeling sad? It’s rather baffling to see them included. 

- Amazing Spider-Man v2 #36, 2001
